TITLE: Creating a Plugin with State Management
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to implement a plugin with its own state store and methods to update that state when events occur.

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
const MyPlugin = createPlatePlugin({
  key: 'myPlugin',
  options: {
    count: 0,
  },
}).extend(({ editor, plugin, setOption }) => ({
  handlers: {
    onClick: () => {
      setOption('count', 1);
    },
  },
}));
```

