TITLE: Defining Node Types in Slate
DESCRIPTION: Defines the basic type hierarchy for nodes in Slate. The hierarchy includes TNode as the base type (which can be Editor, Element, or Text), Descendant for child nodes (Element or Text), and Ancestor for parent nodes (Editor or Element).

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type TNode = Editor | TElement | TText;

type Descendant = Element | Text
type Ancestor = Editor | Element
```

