TITLE: Overriding Editor Methods
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the overrideEditor method to modify existing editor functionality while maintaining access to the original implementations.

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
const CustomPlugin = createPlatePlugin({
  key: 'custom',
}).overrideEditor(({ editor, tf: { deleteForward }, api: { isInline } }) => ({
  // Override transforms
  transforms: {
    deleteForward(options) {
      // Custom logic before deletion
      console.info('Deleting forward...');

      // Call original transform
      deleteForward(options);

      // Custom logic after deletion
      console.info('Deleted forward');
    },
  },
  // Override API methods
  api: {
    isInline(element) {
      // Custom inline element check
      if (element.type === 'custom-inline') {
        return true;
      }

      // Fall back to original behavior
      return isInline(element);
    },
  },
}));
```

